## Best Practices

### DO ✅

```ruby
# Pass IDs, not ActiveRecord objects
ArticleNotificationJob.perform_later(@article.id)

# Use find_each for large datasets
def perform
  User.active.find_each do |user|
    process_user(user)
  end
end

# Keep jobs focused (single responsibility)
class SendWelcomeEmailJob < ApplicationJob
  def perform(user_id)
    user = User.find(user_id)
    WelcomeMailer.welcome(user).deliver_now
  end
end

# Use appropriate queues
class UrgentNotificationJob < ApplicationJob
  queue_as :urgent
end

# Configure retries appropriately
retry_on TimeoutError, wait: 10.seconds, attempts: 5
discard_on ActiveRecord::RecordNotFound
```

### DON'T ❌

```ruby
# Don't pass ActiveRecord objects (serialize to ID)
# ArticleNotificationJob.perform_later(@article)  # Bad!

# Don't load all records at once
# User.all.each { |user| process(user) }  # Bad!

# Don't put business logic in jobs
# Keep business logic in models/services
# Jobs should orchestrate, not implement

# Don't ignore error handling
# Add retry/discard configuration

# Don't create jobs for everything
# Simple operations can be synchronous
```

